    {
      "id": "jshell-501-intro",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "# JShell 501 — Expert: Data Pipelines & Functional Patterns\n\nThis notebook builds toward a **complete functional data pipeline** — the kind used in real ETL systems, analytics engines, and data-intensive services.\n\nWe'll cover the building blocks first, then assemble them into a mini analytics system.\n\n## Roadmap\n1. **Custom functional interfaces** — define your own `@FunctionalInterface`\n2. **Method references** — the 4 kinds: static, instance, instance of arbitrary type, constructor\n3. **Function composition** — `andThen`, `compose`, `Predicate.and/or/negate`\n4. **BiFunction and higher-order functions** — functions that take or return functions\n5. **Parallel streams** — easy multi-core processing\n6. **End-to-end pipeline** — load → validate → transform → aggregate → report\n\n> **Prerequisite:** You should be comfortable with Streams (JShell 301) and Modern Java (JShell 401).",
      "output": "",
